```The small figure starts making a noise that the God cannot understand at first, it examines the figure closely. A small human whelp, drops of water streaming from its eyes and blood still dripping from a wound on its hand. The God looks around taking in the summoning circle crudely drawn in chalk, at his feet sits a replica of an animal, with long ears and a pink nose, and a dagger stabbed into its stomach.

“But… What happened to God Mister?” 

The God examines the human closely before sitting in the circle and sighing. The God reaches a tentacle out to the human's hand, and suddenly the wound is stitched back together with ribbons of flesh.
“She wouldn't have wanted you to harm your form child.” ```

So I noticed that "generate more" doesn't seem to work properly half the time, and I _kinda_ think I know what's causing the issue.
Basically, whenever you generate more, it'll always add the character's name to the prompt at the end of your prompt, thus confusing the AI and making it think it's starting a new sentence. So I think, anyway.
If you click the Adapter Information (i) it'll show a sentence like
```Joe: So I had that new sandwhich at the corner store, the one by
Joe: [no text]```
I think this is the reason it's not continuing a previous sentence but starts a new one, cuz it starts from a new "Joe:" each time.

**HOW TO FIX: "The model is writing as me!"**
1. Make sure you're using the right instruct-prompt for the model
2. Make sure `Include Name` is enabled (same place as the instruct prompts were set)
3. Write explicit instructions in the system prompt or character card (`Avoid writing actions or speech for {{user}}` or something)
4. Fill the chat log with interactions in the writing style you want (may need to edit a few replies by hand to get what you want).
Bonus 5. Just get used to editing replies, because the big models do this too sometimes.
